<h5>
    Implications
</h5>
<ul>
    <li>
        Potential energy is always held by a system, never an object alone.
    </li>
    <li>
        Potential energy is always related to a <strong>conservative force</strong>.
        <ul>
            <li>
                Gravitational potential energy is related to graivty.
            </li>
            <li>
                Elastic potential energy is related to the elastic force.
            </li>
            <li>
                Electrostatic potential energy is related to the electrostatic force.
                This is the force that would be contained in a two positive charges close to
                each other, with the potential to fly apart!
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>


